<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="56" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1694,2030]" pageId="11" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,292,1694,1720]" pageId="11" pageNumber="56">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet ‘peristeriana’ is derived from the name of the 
<typeStatus box="[1084,1134,1694,1720]" pageId="11" pageNumber="56">type</typeStatus>
locality (Mt. Peristéri) in combination with the Latin suffix -ana.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="59" pageId="11" pageNumber="56" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1694,2030]" box="[197,933,1771,1798]" pageId="11" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,349,1771,1797]" pageId="11" pageNumber="56">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[356,411,1772,1797]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="56">Size.</emphasis>
Very small, wing length 
<quantity box="[705,839,1772,1798]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" metricValueMax="3.6" metricValueMin="3.2" pageId="11" pageNumber="56" unit="mm" value="3.4" valueMax="3.6" valueMin="3.2">3.2–3.6mm</quantity>
(n= 
<number box="[890,920,1772,1798]" pageId="11" pageNumber="56" value="16.0">16</number>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1694,2030]" lastBlockId="12.[151,1437,152,487]" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="57" pageId="11" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis box="[197,266,1811,1836]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="56">Male.</emphasis>
Frons at narrowest point distinctly wider than distance between inner margins of posterior ocelli, frontal vitta at this point much wider than combined width of narrow parafrontals. Parafacial at narrowest point fully as wide as postpedicel. Also gena in lateral aspect relatively broad; genal setae standing in multiple rows. Arista barely longer than antenna measured from base of scape to tip of postpedicel; aristomere 
<number box="[1421,1436,1926,1952]" pageId="11" pageNumber="56" value="3.0">3</number>
thickened on basal third. Palp slightly shorter than fore tarsomere 
<number box="[962,978,1965,1991]" pageId="11" pageNumber="56" value="1.0">1</number>
; prementum slightly longer than fore tarsomere 
<number box="[276,291,2004,2030]" pageId="11" pageNumber="56" value="1.0">1</number>
, covered in thin dusting allowing a blackish subshine on lateral parts. Thorax with a matt black shine through thin ash-grey dusting; on mesonotum with a brown tinge on posterior part and in certain aspects with a weak pattern of three darker stripes. Presutural acrostichal rows in front no farther apart than their distance to dorsocentral rows; middle pair of acrostichals strongly enlarged; a few setulae present between rows. Notopleuron without accessory setulae. Proepimerals 
<number box="[871,915,268,294]" pageId="12" pageNumber="57" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5</number>
setae and setulae. Wing base and calyptrae dark brown infuscated; knob of halter ochreous-yellow. Abdomen relatively short and broad; with a distinct dark subshine through thin greyish dusting that in posterior aspects reveals a poorly defined black pattern consisting of a broad mid-dorsal stripe and laterally tapering anterior bands on tergites II–V. Terminalia (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 7" captionStartId="4.[151,271,1854,1878]" captionTargetBox="[233,1349,208,1818]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[223,1363,197,1829]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 7. Botanophila spp. 1. Seed head of Ranunculus repens L. with supposed egg of B. helviana (arrow). 2. Uterine egg, B. saliciphila. 3. Left labellum, B. kitadakeana, female. 4. Male sternite V, B. helviana. 5, 6. Hypopygium in caudal and lateral aspects, B. miniatura. 7. Gonites, phallus (with ejaculatory apodeme) and phallapodeme in lateral aspect, phallus in anterior aspect, B. peristeriana. Scale bar = 1.0 mm (1); 0.25 mm (2); 0.1 mm (3 – 7)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274869/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="57">Figs. 7</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[181,260,422,448]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 28" captionStartId="12.[151,274,1967,1991]" captionTargetBox="[196,1367,568,1929]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[190,1396,545,1942]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 28. Botanophila peristeriana. 25, 26. Hypopygium in caudal and lateral aspects. 27. Oviscapt, flat mounted. 28. Spermathecae. Scale bar = 0.1 mm (25, 26); 0.25 mm (27, 28)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274875/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="57">
25, 
<number box="[226,260,422,448]" pageId="12" pageNumber="57" value="26.0">26</number>
</figureCitation>
): Cerci distally, as in 
<taxonomicName box="[518,696,423,448]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Botanophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kitadakeana">
<emphasis box="[518,696,423,448]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="57">B. kitadakeana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[713,801,422,448]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 17" captionStartId="7.[151,274,1405,1429]" captionTargetBox="[296,1298,207,1365]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[275,1312,197,1380]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 17. Botanophila kitadakeana. 15, 16. Hypopygium in caudal and lateral aspects. 17. Oviscapt, flat mounted. Scale bar = 0.1 mm (15, 16); 0.25 mm (17)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274872/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="57">
Fig. 
<number box="[769,801,422,448]" pageId="12" pageNumber="57" value="15.0">15</number>
</figureCitation>
), without a median prong, but that species has a very different shape of surstylus (
<figureCitation box="[485,569,461,487]" captionStart="FIGURES 15 – 17" captionStartId="7.[151,274,1405,1429]" captionTargetBox="[296,1298,207,1365]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[275,1312,197,1380]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 15 – 17. Botanophila kitadakeana. 15, 16. Hypopygium in caudal and lateral aspects. 17. Oviscapt, flat mounted. Scale bar = 0.1 mm (15, 16); 0.25 mm (17)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274872/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="57">
Fig. 
<number box="[539,569,461,487]" pageId="12" pageNumber="57" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
) as seen in lateral aspect.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274875/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="57" targetBox="[196,1367,568,1929]" targetPageId="12">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1967,2026]" pageId="12" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,358,1967,1991]" pageId="12" pageNumber="57">FIGURES 25–28.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[366,649,1968,1991]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Botanophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peristeriana">
<emphasis box="[366,649,1968,1991]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="57">Botanophila peristeriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[665,743,1967,1991]" pageId="12" pageNumber="57">25, 26.</emphasis>
Hypopygium in caudal and lateral aspects. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1241,1276,1967,1991]" pageId="12" pageNumber="57">27.</emphasis>
Oviscapt, flat mounted. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[257,291,2002,2026]" pageId="12" pageNumber="57">28.</emphasis>
Spermathecae. Scale bar = 0.1mm (25, 26); 0.25mm (27, 28).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274876/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="58" targetBox="[209,1369,184,1598]" targetPageId="13">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,1599,1657]" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,360,1599,1623]" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">FIGURES 29–31.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[369,638,1600,1623]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Botanophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saliciphila">
<emphasis box="[369,638,1600,1623]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Botanophila saliciphila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[654,733,1599,1623]" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">29, 30.</emphasis>
Hypopygium in caudal and lateral aspects. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1238,1273,1599,1623]" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">31.</emphasis>
Oviscapt, flat mounted. Scale bar = 0.1mm (29, 30); 0.25mm (31).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1704,2000]" lastBlockId="14.[151,1437,152,526]" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="59" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis box="[197,302,1704,1729]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Female.</emphasis>
Parafacial at narrowest point about same width as postpedicel. Gena in lateral aspect comparatively broad with genal setae at least in front standing in three rows. Arista barely longer than antenna measured from base of scape to tip of postpedicel; aristomere 
<number box="[880,895,1781,1807]" pageId="13" pageNumber="58" value="3.0">3</number>
thickened on basal third. Palp slightly shorter than fore tarsomere 
<number box="[393,409,1820,1846]" pageId="13" pageNumber="58" value="1.0">1</number>
; prementum slightly longer than fore tarsomere 
<number box="[993,1008,1820,1846]" pageId="13" pageNumber="58" value="1.0">1</number>
, covered in thin dusting allowing a strong blackish subshine on lateral parts. Thorax appearing lighter as in male, but still with a matt, dark subshine through thin, dark-grey dusting; three dark-brown mesonotal stripes faintly indicated in certain aspects, especially in front of scutellum. Presutural acrostichal rows in front no farther apart than their distance to dorsocentral rows; middle pair of acrostichals strongly enlarged; a few setulae present between rows. Notopleuron without accessory setulae. Proepimerals 
<number box="[871,915,152,178]" pageId="14" pageNumber="59" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4</number>
setae and setulae. Wing base and calyptrae lightly brownish infuscated; knob of halter ochreous-yellow. Abdomen appearing uniformly shiny black through very thin layer of brown dusting. Oviscapt (
<figureCitation box="[760,848,229,255]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 28" captionStartId="12.[151,274,1967,1991]" captionTargetBox="[196,1367,568,1929]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[190,1396,545,1942]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 28. Botanophila peristeriana. 25, 26. Hypopygium in caudal and lateral aspects. 27. Oviscapt, flat mounted. 28. Spermathecae. Scale bar = 0.1 mm (25, 26); 0.25 mm (27, 28)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274875/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="59">
Fig. 
<number box="[814,848,229,255]" pageId="14" pageNumber="59" value="28.0">28</number>
</figureCitation>
): Almost as in 
<taxonomicName box="[1023,1179,229,254]" class="Insecta" family="Anthomyiidae" genus="Botanophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saliciphila">
<emphasis box="[1023,1179,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="59">B. saliciphila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1195,1279,229,255]" captionStart="FIGURES 29 – 31" captionStartId="13.[151,275,1599,1623]" captionTargetBox="[209,1369,184,1598]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[195,1389,171,1609]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 29 – 31. Botanophila saliciphila. 29, 30. Hypopygium in caudal and lateral aspects. 31. Oviscapt, flat mounted. Scale bar = 0.1 mm (29, 30); 0.25 mm (31)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274876/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="59">
Fig. 
<number box="[1249,1279,229,255]" pageId="14" pageNumber="59" value="31.0">31</number>
</figureCitation>
) except cerci more angular subbasally along outer margin. Spermathecae (
<figureCitation box="[877,965,268,294]" captionStart="FIGURES 25 – 28" captionStartId="12.[151,274,1967,1991]" captionTargetBox="[196,1367,568,1929]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[190,1396,545,1942]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 25 – 28. Botanophila peristeriana. 25, 26. Hypopygium in caudal and lateral aspects. 27. Oviscapt, flat mounted. 28. Spermathecae. Scale bar = 0.1 mm (25, 26); 0.25 mm (27, 28)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/274875/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="59">
Fig. 
<number box="[934,965,268,294]" pageId="14" pageNumber="59" value="28.0">28</number>
</figureCitation>
) normal for the species group, modestsized and with long, very slender ducts.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
